<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8563> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8563" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 735, footnote 101" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7177> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7177" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 165. Leg., envoy 170-168. See MRR 1.426, no. b. He was sent late in 170 along with C. Popillius Laenas (18), by the Consul, A. Hostilius Mancinus, to visit the Greek cities and strengthen their attachment to the Roman side, and was honored in a decree of Argos. Both envoys returned early in 169 to Hostilius, then proconsul. See P. Charneux, BCH 81, 1957, 181-202; and on the dating, see below on C. Popillius Laenas (18). Cos. 172. Praetor 168. He was honored by Echinus while in command of the fleet in the war with Perseus (Aepig. 1971, no. 450; see MRR 1.428; J. M. Reynolds, JRS 66, 1976, 178).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2843> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2843" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "While they were in Syria Octavius was killed by Leptines of Laodiceia (Polyb. 31.11.1, 12.4, and 33.5; 32.2.1-8, 3.1-3, and 10-13; Cic. Phil. 9.4, and 7, and 14; Diod. 31.29; Plin. NH 34.24; App. Syr. 46-47; Obseq. 15; Zon. 9.25)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2836> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2836" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent to the East with instructions to disarm Syria, now ruled by the minor son of Antiochus IV, burn the warships and hamstring the elephants, and to survey the situation in Macedonia, Galatia, and Cappadocia, also to reconcile the two Ptolemies in Alexandria (Polyb. 31.2.9-14, and 8.4-8; Cic. Phil. 9.4; App. Syr. 46; cf. Durrbach and Roussel, I. de Délos 3.1429, on Octavius' offering at Delos; also Holleaux, {Gr}. 157f.). See 162, Legates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2835> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2835" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Pliny (NH 34.24) has confused this embassy with that of C. Popillius Laenas (see 168), and has Octavius play a similar role." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2811> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2811" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Fin. 1.24; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 50f., 123, 460f.; Obseq. 13; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; cf. Didasc. Ter. Hec.; and on Octavius, Fest. 188 L. See Holleaux, {Gr}. 157f.; BCH 54 (1930) 10f., 39; Daux, Delphes 352f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2784> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2784" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Propraetor in command of the fleet (Act. Tr. Cap. and Urbisalv., Degrassi 80f., 338f., 556). He transported Aemilius Paullus' army and booty home and celebrated a naval triumph (Liv. 45.28.8, 29.3, 33.7, 35.4-5, and 42.2-3; Act. Tr. Cap. and Urbisalv.; Diod. 31.8.9; Vell. 1.9.5-6; Plin. 34.13; Fest. 188 L; cf. SIG\n     650). He built the Portious Octavia and a house on the Palatine (Cic. Off. 1.138; Vell. 2.1.2; Plin. NH 34.13; Fest. 188 L; cf. Res Gest. D. Aug. 19)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2731> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2731" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Election Liv. 44.17.5 Provinces and armies Liv. 44.17.9-10." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2728> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2728" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cn. Octavius succeeded M. Claudius Marcellus. Liv. 44.18.7; Fest. 188 L." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2721> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2721" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent about the Greek communities by Hostilius to strengthen their attachment to the Roman side (Polyb. 28.3-5; Liv. 43.17.2-9). Popillius was placed in command of Ambracia (43.17.10). See Lübker no. 3." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2617> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2617" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fest. 188 L." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2616> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2616" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "This aedileship is tentatively dated in 172 rather than in 170 by Seidel (38) and Münzer (RE) because of his associations with Popillius, the Consul of this year." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10169> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10169" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Naval Triumph ex Macedonia et rege Perse. MRR I.434, Itgenshorst no. 201, Rich no. 200." .
